## Data Assets

All assets are resolved relative to `Data/` (the VS debugger working directory).

| Asset | UUID (from Config.json) | Role |
|-------|------------------------|------|
| `Assets/App/Config.json` | — | Provides the four UUID strings on first frame |
| `Assets/App/UI/SandboxUI.json` | `e48eb073-fcb1-44eb-a3b0-eb2f186a5831` | Root UI layout with two children: a text widget (`uuidui1`) and an image widget (`uuidui2`) |
| `opensans/OpenSans-Regular.ttf` | `79e69fe7-4e41-42b0-a47f-a4bb8040f02f` | Default font for all text draws |
| `Checkerboard.png` | `e3afff59-1ee8-4396-b9ed-b093dd521f91` | Texture assigned to the image widget in `SandboxUI.json` |

`SandboxUI.json` defines:
- Root: 1280×720, left/top alignment.
- Child `uuidui1` (the text widget, UUID `92345678-9abc-def0-1234-56789abcdef2`): 100×100, center-aligned, contains a `text` element with the string `"sSample\nUI"`.
- Child `uuidui2` (the image widget, UUID `92345678-9abc-def0-1234-56789abcdef1`): 400×400, left/top, references texture `Checkerboard.png`.

Note: the UUID naming in the JSON is inverted relative to the variable names in `SandboxUISingletonComponent` — `uuidui1` in config maps to the text child and `uuidui2` maps to the image child.

