## Unit Tests

Test files: `Code/UT/UT_Sandbox/ConfigLoaderSystemTest.cpp`, `SampleUISystemTest.cpp`

All tests use the Catch2 framework and the `pg::World::Create()` / `pg::World::GetRegistryDirect()` test-only API.

### ConfigLoaderSystem tests

| Test case | What it verifies |
|-----------|-----------------|
| `CreatesConfigOnFirstFrame` | No component before `Update`; exactly one `SampleUIConfigSingletonComponent` after one `Update`. |
| `DoesNotDuplicateWhenConfigExists` | Pre-seeding one component; system leaves count at 1 after `Update`. |
| `LoadedConfigHasNonNullUUIDs` | All four UUID fields (`m_UUIDUI1`, `m_UUIDUI2`, `m_DefaultFontID`, `m_MainLayoutID`) are non-null after `Update`. |
| `DeclareAccessIsCorrect` | `readSet` and `addSet` both contain `SampleUIConfigSingletonComponent`. |

### SampleUISystem tests

| Test case | What it verifies |
|-----------|-----------------|
| `NoOpWithoutResourceMap` | Config present but no `ResourceMapSingletonComponent` → no `SampleUISingletonComponent` created. |
| `NoOpWithoutConfig` | Resource map present but no config → no `SampleUISingletonComponent` created. |
| `CreatesComponentsOnFirstFrame` | Both guards satisfied → `SampleUISingletonComponent` visible after one `Update`. |
| `CreatedComponentHasFontIDFromConfig` | `m_FontID` on the created component equals `m_DefaultFontID` from the config component. |
| `CreatesOrthographicCameraOnFirstFrame` | `OrthographicCameraComponent` is created alongside `SampleUISingletonComponent`. |
| `DeclareAccessIsCorrect` | All four access sets (readSet, writeSet, addSet, inframeAddSet) contain exactly the declared component types. |
